<p>The state's humid subtropical climate presents unique challenges and opportunities for HVAC systems. Mississippi experiences hot, humid summers with average temperatures reaching the mid-90s, requiring efficient cooling systems for approximately 7-8 months of the year. Mild winters mean heating demands are moderate, making heat pumps an excellent choice for year-round comfort. The combination of high cooling loads and abundant solar resources makes Mississippi an ideal location for solar-powered HVAC systems, where homeowners can significantly offset their highest energy consumption periods with peak solar production.</p>

