<h2>Mississippi Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Mississippi offers several valuable incentives that make solar and HVAC investments more attractive for homeowners:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal 30% Solar Tax Credit:</strong> The Investment Tax Credit (ITC) allows homeowners to deduct 30% of solar installation costs from their federal taxes through 2032. This credit covers equipment, installation, and related costs, with no cap on the credit amount. The credit can be carried forward to future tax years if it exceeds current tax liability. For a \$20,000 solar installation, this represents \$6,000 in direct tax savings.</li>

<li><strong>Property Tax Exemption:</strong> Mississippi exempts the added value of renewable energy systems from property tax assessments. This means homeowners won't pay additional property taxes on the increased home value created by solar installations, typically saving \$100-300 annually depending on local tax rates and system size.</li>

<li><strong>Mississippi Power Rebates:</strong> The utility offers rebates for energy-efficient HVAC equipment, including \$300-800 for qualifying heat pumps with SEER ratings of 15 or higher. Smart thermostat rebates of \$50-100 are also available. The PowerSaver program provides additional incentives for whole-home efficiency improvements.</li>

<li><strong>Entergy Mississippi Programs:</strong> Entergy offers the Energy Smart program with rebates up to \$1,000 for high-efficiency HVAC systems. Heat pump water heater rebates of \$300-500 and duct sealing incentives help maximize home efficiency. The utility also provides free energy audits to identify improvement opportunities.</li>

<li><strong>PACE Financing:</strong> Some Mississippi counties offer Property Assessed Clean Energy (PACE) financing, allowing homeowners to finance solar and efficiency improvements through property tax assessments. This provides long-term, low-interest financing that transfers with property ownership.</li>
</ul>

